          <title locale="en">Cross-Cultural Dimensions of Existential Therapy</title>
          <abstract locale="en">&lt;p&gt;Existential therapy is often criticised as a Western-centric approach. This paper challenges that view by examining parallels between existential philosophy and Eastern thought, particularly Zen Buddhism and Japanese concepts of impermanence.&lt;/p&gt;</abstract>
          <copyrightHolder locale="en">Yuki Tanaka</copyrightHolder>
          <copyrightYear>2024</copyrightYear>
          <keywords locale="en">
            <keyword>existential</keyword>
            <keyword>cross-cultural</keyword>
            <keyword>Zen Buddhism</keyword>
            <keyword>impermanence</keyword>
